  "content": "pture`\nExpected: all 3 tests PASS\n\n**Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add crates/corvia-kernel/src/retriever.rs crates/corvia-kernel/src/lib.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(m3.2): Retriever trait + VectorRetriever — vector search with visibility filtering\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 5: GraphExpandRetriever\n\nVector search + graph edge expansion. The differentiating retriever.\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `crates/corvia-kernel/src/retriever.rs`\n\n**Step 1: Write the failing test**\n\nAdd to the `tests` module in `retriever.rs`:\n\n```rust\n    #[tokio::test]\n    async fn test_graph_expand_retriever_adds_neighbors() {\n        let dir = tempfile::tempdir().unwrap();\n        let store = Arc::new(LiteStore::open(dir.path(), 3).unwrap()) as Arc<dyn QueryableStore>;\n        let engine = Arc::new(MockEngine) as Arc<dyn InferenceEngine>;\n        store.init_schema().await.unwrap();\n\n        let mut idx = 0_usize;\n        let mut next_emb = || { idx += 1; vec![1.0, idx as f32 * 0.001, 0.0] };\n\n        // Entry A: will be found by vector search\n        let mut ea = KnowledgeEntry::new(\"auth module\".into(), \"proj\".into(), \"v1\".into())\n            .with_embedding(next_emb());\n        ea.entry_status = EntryStatus::Merged;\n        store.insert(&ea).await.unwrap();\n\n        // Entry B: will NOT be found by vector search (different scope won't work,\n        // so we use graph to expand to it)\n        let mut eb = KnowledgeEntry::new(\"auth middleware\".into(), \"proj\".into(), \"v1\".into())\n            .with_embedding(next_emb());\n        eb.entry_status = EntryStatus::Merged;\n        store.insert(&eb).await.unwrap();\n",
